ption%3EThe%20tiny%20forest%2C%20also%20known%20as%20the%20Manhattan%20Healing%20Forest%2C%20sits%20at%20the%20southern%20end%20of%20Roosevelt%20Island.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20SUGi%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESharon%20Bean%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20Syracuse%2C%20New%20York%2C%20drove%20down%20to%20volunteer%20at%20the%20planting%20in%20honor%20of%20her%20sister%2C%20Kat%20Livingston%2C%20an%20avid%20gardener%20who%20died%20in%20January%20of%20cancer.%20Bean%2C%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Navajo%20Nation%20who%20grew%20up%20in%20New%20Mexico%2C%20believes%20kids%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20need%20to%20connect%20with%20nature.%20%26quot%3BThey%20should%20learn%20plants%20first%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0our%20nature%20first%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0people%20second%2C%20things%20last.%20And%20it%20seems%20like%20we%20reversed%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Volunteers%20place%20native%20trees%20and%20shrubs%20in%20pre-dug%20holes%20in%20what%20will%20become%20a%20pocket%20forest%20on%20Roosevelt%20Island%20in%20New%20York%20City.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6615a3e316bde8d4ead71839%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22850%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EVolunteers%20plant%20native%20trees%20and%20shrubs%20in%20pre-dug%20holes.%3Cp%3EEliza%20Relman%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20being%20designed%20as%20an%20urban%20paradise%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0a%20small%2C%20affordable%20town%20with%20plenty%20of%20green%20space%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0the%20island%20%26quot%3Bis%20sitting%20on%20a%20lot%20of%20untapped%20potential%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20resident%20and%20urban%20researcher%20Tayana%20Panova.%20Its%20urban%20design%2C%20Panova%20said%2C%20could%20do%20more%20to%20bring%20people%20together.%20%26quot%3BIt%20has%20the%20bones%20of%20a%20great%20main%20street%20with%20a%20lovely%20main%20square%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20but%20there's%20littl