ace%20affects%20the%20likelihood%20a%20job%20applicant%20will%20get%20a%20callback%20for%20an%20entry-level%20job.%3Cp%3EJustin%20Sullivan%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EResearchers%20studied%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblack-job-candidates-more-likely-to-face-discriminatory-questions-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eracial%20bias%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20hiring%20by%20sending%20over%2083%2C000%20fake%C2%A0r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%C2%A0to%20big%20US%20companies.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ER%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20with%20Black-sounding%20names%20were%20often%20less%20likely%20to%20get%20callbacks.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENow%2C%20the%20researchers%20are%20naming%20names%20among%20the%20more%20than%20100%20Fortune%20500%20companies%20involved.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20researchers%20determined%20that%20having%20a%20name%20like%20Emily%20or%20Greg%20on%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20made%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fracial-discrimination-the-job-market-study-black-names-applications-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeasier%20to%20get%20a%20callback%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20a%20job%20than%20having%20a%20name%20like%20Lakisha%20or%20Jamal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20researchers%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbfi.uchicago.edu%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FA-Discrimination-Report-Cardv3.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enaming%20names%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20not%20of%20potential%20employees%2C%20but%20of%20companies%20and%20industries%20that%20seem%20to%20favor%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20from%20job%20candidates%20who%20appear%20white%20over%20those%20whose%20names%20suggest%20they're%20Black.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20auto%20services%20industry%20was%20among%20those%20most%20likely%20to%20show%20a%20preference%20for%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20containing%20white-sounding%20names.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20determine%20which%20names%20might%20disadvantage%20job%20applicants%2C%20researchers%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Chicago%20and%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20Berkeley%2C%20sent%20more%20than%2083%2C000%20fake%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20to%20more%20than%20100%20big%20US%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20best%20cases%2C%20employers%20went%20for%20white-seeming%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20more%20frequently%20than%20Black-seeming%20ones%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbfi.uchicago.edu%2Finsight%2Fresearch-summary%2Fa-discrimination-report-card%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eonly%20slightly%20or%20not%20at%20all%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20researchers%20said.%20But%20in%20the%20most%20extreme%20instances%2C%20those%20doing%20the%20hiring%20favored%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20that%20might%20be%20presumed%20to%20be%20from%20white%20candidates%20by%2024%25%2C%20on%20average.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20findings%20illustrate%20how%20difficult%20it%20can%20be%20for%20many%20job%20seekers%20%E2%80%94%20even%20in%20a%20strong%20labor%20market%20%E2%80%94%20to%20find%20work.%20Already%2C%20some%20people%20in%20fields%20like%20tech%20who%20have%20seen%20cuts%20in%20recent%20years%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdouble-digit-interviews-multiple-reviews-burned-out-exhausted-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eapplying%20to%20job%20after%20job%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20little%20luck.%20Having%20to%20overcome%20race%20as%20an%20obstacle%20can%20make%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsimple-cover-letter-example-unemployed-job-search-never-hear-back-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehunt%20all%20the%20more%20difficult%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPutting%20the%20names%20out%20there%20in%20the%20public%20domain%20is%20to%20move%20away%20from%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20performative%20allyship%20that%20you%20see%20with%20these%20companies%2C%20saying%2C%20'Oh%2C%20we%20value%20inclusivity%20and%20diversity%2C'%26quot%3B%20Pat%20Kline%2C%20a%20Berkeley%20economics%20professor%20involved%20in%20the%20study%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2F2024%2F04%2F11%2F1243713272%2Fresume-bias-study-white-names-black-names%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20told%20National%20Public%20Radio%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20trying%20to%20create%20kind%20of%20an%20objective%20ground%20truth%20here.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20some%20companies%20fared%20worse%20than%20others.%20The%20authors%20said%20the%20worst%2020%25%20of%20companies%20accounted%20for%20about%20half%20of%20the%20discrimination%20Black%20applicants%20faced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGenuine%20Parts%20Company%2C%20parent%20of%20NAPA%20Auto%20Parts%2C%20and%20AutoNation%2C%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20auto%20retailers%20in%20the%20US%2C%20were%20among%20those%20researchers%20ranked%20lowest%20in%20their%20assessment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20did%20caution%20that%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20experiment%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0sending%20fake%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20to%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20results%20in%20%26quot%3Bonly%20noisy%26quot%3B%20estimates%20of%20a%20company's%20potential%20discrimination.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20company%20where%20researchers%20identified%20disparate%20response%20rates%20for%20candidates%20was%20Costco.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20for%20Genuine%20Parts%20Company%2C%20AutoNation%2C%20and%20Costco%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider%20ahead%20of%20publication.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20108%20companies%20researchers%20sent%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20to%2C%20among%20the%20best%20performers%20were%20car-rental%20company%20Avis%20Budget%20Group%20and%20the%20grocery%20chain%20Kroger.%20Representatives%20from%20both%20companies%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20deemed%20names%20as%20%26quot%3Bracially%20distinctive%26quot%3B%20if%20more%20than%20nine%20in%2010%20people%20called%20that%20were%20of%20the%20same%20race%2C%20according%20to%20NPR.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20did%20that%20look%20like%20in%20practice%3F%20It%20meant%20pitting%20a%20Brad%20or%20a%20Greg%20against%20a%20Darnell%20or%20a%20Lamar%2C%20NPR%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20findings%20build%20on%20work%20done%20two%20decades%20ago%20by%20University%20of%20Chicago%20researchers%2C%20who%20found%20that%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20with%20white-sounding%20names%20were%2050%25%20more%20likely%20to%20get%20a%20call%20from%20a%20hiring%20manager%20than%20those%20with%20Black-sounding%20names%2C%20the%20university%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20also%20examined%20how%20much%20names%20associated%20with%20a%20particular%20gender%20affect%20an%20applicant's%20success%20in%20getting%20a%20hit.%20Some%20industries%20preferred%20men%2C%20while%20others%20went%20for%20women%20more%20often.%20In%20most%20cases%2C%20however%2C%20gender%20didn't%20appear%20to%20play%20a%20role%20in%20how%20often%20a%20candidate%20got%20a%20callback.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConcerns%20about%20hiring%20bias%20have%20drawn%20attention%20in%20recent%20years%20because%20of%20fears%20that%20artificial%20intelligence%20could%20exacerbate%20inequities%20in%20who%20gets%20a%20shot%20at%20what%20jobs.%20That%20extends%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-racial-bias-job-hiring-report-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efurthering%20racial%20bias%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20researchers%20have%20also%20said%20that%2C%20done%20right%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-help-recruit-hire-employees-tech-women-bias-job-seeking-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20could%20help%20reduce%20bias%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20hiring%20%E2%80%94%20by%20helping%20women%2C%20for%20example%2C%20land%20roles%20in%20fields%20like%20tech%20that%20men%20have%20historically%20dominated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAndreas%20Leibbrandt%2C%20an%20economist%20at%20Australia's%20Monash%20University%2C%20previously%20told%20BI%20that%20if%20AI%20could%20remove%20identifiers%20like%20gender%20%E2%80%94%20or%20names%20associated%20with%20gender%20%E2%80%94%20that%20could%20help%20make%20the%20process%20fairer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20do%20observe%20that%20when%20recruiters%20know%20the%20gender%20of%20the%20applicants%2C%20then%20they%20discriminate%20against%20women.%20When%20we%20remove%20the%20gender%2C%20there%20is%20no%20gender%20difference%2C%26quot%3B%20Leibbrandt%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20kind%20of%20bias%20is%20one%20reason%20Khyati%20Sundaram%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20a%20hiring%20startup%20called%20Applied%2C%20doesn't%20think%20the%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20should%20be%20central%20to%20getting%20a%20job.%20Instead%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhiring-tests-impact-on-resume-and-employment-2024-3%3Futm_source%3Dcopy-link%26utm_medium%3Dreferral%26utm_content%3Dtopbar%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Escreening%20for%20skills%3C%2Fa%3E%20through%20tests%20could%20help%20make%20the%20process%20fairer%2C%20she%20previously%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKline%2C%20the%20Berkeley%20professor%2C%20told%20NPR%20he%20and%20his%20fellow%20researchers%20hoped%20people%20would%20focus%20as%20much%20on%20the%20companies%20doing%20better%20with%20equitable%20hiring%20as%20the%20laggards%20because%20doing%20so%20could%20help%20other%20companies%20learn%20how%20to%20curb%20racial%20bias.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20if%20it's%20true%2C%20from%20these%20insights%20in%20psychology%20and%20behavioral%20economics%2C%20that%20individuals%20are%20inevitably%20going%20to%20carry%20biases%20along%20with%20them%2C%20it's%20not%20automatic%20that%20those%20individual%20biases%20will%20translate%20into%20organizational%20biases%2C%26quot%3B%20Kline%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-display-race-gender-bias-when-