Persian%20Gulf%2C%20the%20Sheraton%20Grand%20Doha%20Resort%20%26amp%3B%20Convention%20Hotel%20is%20an%20outlier%20among%20the%20skinny%20skyscrapers%20that%20dominate%20the%20skyline%20of%20Doha%2C%20Qatar's%20capital.%20In%201982%20the%20country's%20ruling%20Al%20Thani%20family%20ordered%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20five-star%20hotel%2C%20with%20its%20private%20beach%20and%20opulent%20marble%20lobby.%20Today%20the%20site%20functions%20as%20both%20luxury%20resort%20and%20nerve%20center%20of%20crisis%20diplomacy.%20Here%20warring%20factions%20from%20the%20Taliban%20and%20African%20militias%20have%20convened%2C%20and%20diplomats%20from%20Russia%2C%20the%20US%20and%20Iran%20have%20crossed%20paths%20in%20hallways.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20only-in-Qatar%20milieu%20embodies%20how%20the%20royal%20family%20parlays%20its%20wealth%20into%20geopolitical%20influence%2C%20most%20recently%20as%20a%20key%20mediator%20for%20the%20Israel-Hamas%20war.%20The%20rulers%20have%20turned%20Qatar%20into%20a%20vital%20energy%20supplier%2C%20prominent%20investor%2C%20World%20Cup%20host%2C%20university%20funder%20and%20conflict%20intermediary%20occasionally%20tinged%20with%20controversy%20involving%20corruption%20allegations%20or%20human-rights%20concerns.%20Yet%20their%20strategic%20spending%20ultimately%20comes%20back%20to%20one%20thing%3A%20building%20Qatar%20into%20an%20international%20brand%20that%20can%20underpin%20its%20existence%20and%20the%20family's%20longevity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20finance%20these%20ambitions%2C%20the%20Al%20Thanis%20have%20tapped%20Qatar's%20state%20resources%2C%20along%20with%20their%20personal%20wealth.%20The%20royal%20family's%20holdings%20alone%20amount%20to%20at%20least%20%24150%20billion%2C%20according%20to%20an%20estimate%20by%20the%20Bloomberg%20Billionaires%20Index.%20That%20figure%20excludes%20government%20money%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Qatar%20Investment%20Authority's%20(QIA)%20%24450%20billion%20in%20assets%2C%20including%20the%20Sheraton%20Grand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-04%2F7ab5or28_qatar-royal-family-bloomberg-_625x300_14_April_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPhoto%20Credit%3A%20Bloomberg%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVulnerable%20amid%20powerful%20neighbours%2C%20the%20Al%20Thanis%20are%20leveraging%20that%20wealth%20and%20the%20relationships%20it%20fosters%20to%20become%20an%20indispensable%20broker%20among%20rivals.%20%26quot%3BThey%20are%20constantly%20on%20the%20lookout%20for%20what%20their%20neighbours%20might%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Baraa%20Shiban%2C%20an%20associate%20fellow%20at%20the%20Royal%20United%20Services%20Institute%20in%20London.%20The%20royal%20family%20stands%20out%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20for%20its%20willingness%2C%20often%20at%20US%20behest%2C%20to%20reach%20out%20to%20countries%20and%20groups%20that%20America%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20West%20consider%20pariahs%2C%20Shiban%20says.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Al%20Thanis%20are%20different-they%20are%20very%20dynamic%2C%20and%20that's%20important%2C%26quot%3B%20Shiban%20says.%20A%20host%20to%20exiled%20leaders%20of%20Hamas%2C%20Qatar%20has%20helped%20facilitate%20the%20release%20of%20more%20than%20100%20Israelis%20and%20other%20hostages%20seized%20by%20the%20group%2C%20considered%20terrorists%20by%20the%20US%20and%20European%20Union%2C%20after%20it%20killed%20some%201%2C200%20people%20in%20the%20brutal%20Oct.%207%20rampage%20in%20southern%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThrough%20personal%20holdings%20and%20government%20entities%20they%20oversee%2C%20the%20Qatari%20royals%20have%20assembled%20a%20collection%20of%20properties%20worldwide%20that%20project%20and%20magnify%20their%20influence.%20While%20royals%20in%20Saudi%20Arabia%20and%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%20are%20taking%20a%20similar%20approach%2C%20Qatar%2C%20with%20a%20population%20of%203.1%20million%2C%20is%20far%20smaller.%20Its%20rulers'%20private%20assets%20include%20African%20oil%20fields%2C%20thoroughbred%20horse%20racing%2C%20%247.8%20billion%20worth%20of%20stocks%20listed%20on%20the%20Qatari%20exchange%2C%20grand%20townhouses%20on%20Manhattan's%20Upper%20East%20Side%2C%20French%20retail%20chain%20Printemps%20and%2070%25%20of%20Italian%20luxury%20brand%20Valentino.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeven%20people%20familiar%20with%20the%20royal%20family%20shared%20information%20about%20their%20views%2C%20strategy%20and%20finances%2C%20requesting%20anonymity%20to%20discuss%20sensitive%20information.%20Bloomberg%20examined%20public%20records%20and%20private%20asset%20databases%2C%20and%20interviewed%20people%20close%20to%20their%20holdings%2C%20to%20come%20up%20with%20the%20conservative%20%24150%20billion%20estimate%20of%20the%20family's%20wealth.%20By%20Bloomberg's%20calculations%2C%20it%20surpasses%20the%20value%20of%20the%20holdings%20of%20Saudi%20Arabia's%20royal%20Al%20Sauds%20(%24112%20billion)%20while%20lagging%20those%20of%20the%20UAE's%20Al%20Nahyans%20(%24305%20billion)%20and%20Walmart%20Inc.'s%20Waltons%20(%24281%20billion).%20The%20Al%20Thanis'%20wealth%20is%20poised%20to%20grow%20further%20after%20Qatar%20set%20out%20plans%20in%20late%20February%20to%20expand%20production%20of%20liquefied%20natural%20gas%2C%20which%20has%20transformed%20the%20country's%20economy%20over%20the%20past%2030%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Al%20Thanis%20also%20have%20immense%20political%20power.%20The%20country's%20emir%2C%20Sheikh%20Tamim%20bin%20Hamad%20Al%20Thani%2C%20essentially%20is%20the%20state.%20The%20role%20of%20the%20emir%20is%20%26quot%3Binviolable%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20Qatar's%20constitution%2C%20with%20power%20to%20dissolve%20its%20legislative%20body.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20completely%20different%20sense%20of%20what's%20public%20and%20private%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Allen%20Fromherz%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Georgia%20State%20University%20and%20author%20of%20Qatar%3A%20A%20Modern%20History.%20%26quot%3BTo%20what%20extent%20can%20you%20really%20say%20the%20wealth%20of%20the%20emir%20is%20separate%20from%20the%20wealth%20of%20the%20sovereign%20wealth%20fund%20and%20the%20entire%20Qatari%20economy%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPeople%20familiar%20with%20the%20family%20provided%20a%20rare%20look%20at%20the%20way%20it%20handles%20its%20personal%20finances.%20Every%20Al%20Thani%20above%20the%20age%20of%206%20receives%20a%20monthly%20stipend%20from%20the%20government%2C%20one%20of%20these%20people%20say%3B%20most%20start%20at%20about%206%2C000%20Qatari%20riyals%20(%241%2C645)%20per%20month.%20The%20family%20has%20different%20branches%20across%20which%20responsibilities%20are%20split.%20Some%20members%20engage%20in%20foreign%20affairs%3B%20others%2C%20financial.%20One%20person%20describes%20Sheikh%20Hamad%20bin%20Jassim%20bin%20Jaber%20Al%20Thani%2C%20the%20ex-prime%20minister%20and%20cousin%20of%20the%20former%20emir%2C%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Bfamily%20broker.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt's%20challenging%20to%20give%20an%20accurate%20estimate%20of%20the%20family's%20holdings%20because%20of%20a%20complicated%20network%20of%20ownership%2C%20these%20people%20say%2C%20adding%20that%20Bloomberg's%20estimate%20is%20too%20low.%20In%20a%20written%20statement%2C%20an%20unnamed%20Qatari%20official%20says%20the%20family%20doesn't%20make%20decisions%20for%20the%20country%20unilaterally.%20Qatar's%20legislature%2C%20the%20Consultative%20Assembly%2C%20determines%20the%20state%20budget%20and%20funding.%20The%20government's%20assets%20are%20%26quot%3Bstrategically%20invested%20through%20sovereign%20entities%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Qatar%20Investment%20Authority%20for%20the%20benefit%20of%20future%20generations%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20statement.%20%26quot%3BThe%20investment%20policies%20and%20practices%20of%20these%20entities%20are%20subject%20to%20several%20layers%20of%20independent%20governance.%26quot%3B%20The%20official%20also%20questioned%20Bloomberg's%20methodology%20in%20arriving%20at%20its%20estimate%20of%20the%20family's%20private%20wealth%2C%20calling%20it%20%26quot%3Bhighly%20speculative%2C%20based%20on%20guesswork%20and%20flawed%20extrapolation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20Peninsula%20surrounded%20by%20domineering%20neighbours%2C%20Qatar's%20very%20existence%20was%20never%20a%20given.%20A%20little%20more%20than%20a%20century%20ago%2C%20it%20was%20an%20impoverished%20British%20protectorate.%20The%20Al%20Thanis%20turned%20to%20the%20UK%20after%20fending%20off%20advances%20from%20Bahrain%20and%20the%20Ottoman%20Empire.%20Oil%20was%20first%20discovered%20there%20around%201940%2C%20and%20its%2025.2%20billion%20barrels%20of%20proved%20reserves%20rank%20only%20sixth%20in%20the%20region%2C%20behind%20Kuwait%2C%20according%20to%20US%20government%20data.%20In%201971%2C%20Qatar%20discovered%20vast%20reserves%20of%20natural%20gas%2C%20its%20real%20treasure.%20The%20country%20tapped%20them%20in%20earnest%20in%20the%201990s%20after%20it%20built%20the%20infrastructure%20needed%20to%20export%20the%20gas%20in%20its%20superchilled%20form.%20Demand%20for%20liquefied%20natural%20gas%2C%20or%20LNG%2C%20has%20soared%20in%20recent%20years%20as%20it's%20become%20an%20increasingly%20common%20replacement%20for%20coal.%20Qatar%20draws%20gas%20from%20an%20offshore%20field%20it%20shares%20with%20Iran.%20That%20connection%20has%20promoted%20a%20cordial%20relationship%20between%20the%20two%20nations%20while%20rankling%20the%20US%2C%20which%20considers%20Iran%20a%20state%20sponsor%20of%20terrorism%2C%20and%2C%20at%20times%2C%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20Iran's%20main%20regional%20rival.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20recently%20as%202017%2C%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20the%20UAE%2C%20Bahrain%20and%20Egypt%20embargoed%20Qatar%20as%20punishment%20for%20its%20relationship%20with%20Iran%20and%20its%20alleged%20funding%20of%20terrorist%20groups-a%20claim%20it%20denies.%20It%20was%20an%20existential%20threat%2C%20and%20few%20could've%20predicted%20the%20nation's%20resolve.%20The%20government-backed%20businesses%20that%20airlifted%20cows%20for%20milk.%20The%20QIA%20repatriated%20%2420%20billion%20to%20stabilize%20the%20banking%20system%2C%20and%20new%20trade%20routes%20were%20forged%20through%20Turkey%20and%20Iran.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESheikh%20Hamad%20bin%20Khalifa%20Al%20Thani%2C%20known%20as%20Qatar's%20father%20emir%2C%20pioneered%20the%20strategy%20of%20using%20burgeoning%20wealth%20to%20elevate%20his%20tiny%20country's%20profile%20on%20the%20global%20stage.%20Sandhurst-educated%20Hamad%20ruled%20for%2018%20years%20before%20abdicating%20to%20his%20son%2C%20Tamim%2C%20who%20became%20ruler%20in%202013.%20Hamad%20backed%20the%20founding%20of%20broadcaster%20Al%20Jazeera%20in%20Doha%2C%20positioning%20the%20country%20as%20a%20Middle%20East%20media%20powerhouse.%20He%20also%20established%20the%20QIA%20and%20hosted%20the%20COP%2018%20climate%20change%20conference.%20Hamad%20harnessed%20Qatar's%20gusher%20of%20LNG%20money%20to%20bankroll%20a%20soft-power%20machine%20whose%20traces%20are%20everywhere%3A%20the%20art%20world%2C%20vaunted%20universities%2C%20think%20tanks%2C%20Hollywood%20and%20elite%20sport%20clubs%20such%20as%20French%20soccer%20champion%20Paris%20Saint-Germain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThrough%20state%20vehicles%20like%20the%20QIA%2C%20the%20family%20bought%20London%20icons%20such%20as%20department%20store%20Harrods%20and%20stakes%20in%20the%20Shard%20skyscraper%20and%20Heathrow%20Airport.%20The%20Al%20Thanis%20have%20also%20exerted%20influence%20through%20personal%20capital%3A%20A%20Qatari%20royal%20owns%20Dudley%20House%2C%20a%20historic%2044%2C000-square-foot%20Park%20Lane%20mansion%2C%20where%20he%20once%20hosted%20Queen%20Elizabeth.%20The%20royals'%20Quipco%20investment%20company%20sponsors%20Royal%20Ascot%2C%20the%20annual%20race%20that's%20the%20quintessence%20of%20Britain's%20aristocracy.%20Wealthy%20Qataris%20acquired%20so%20many%20properties%20in%20the%20UK%20capital%20that%20one%20area%20earned%20the%20nickname%20%26quot%3BLittle%20Doha.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EQatar's%20objectives%20are%20more%20than%20financial.%20Trophies%20such%20as%20Claridge's%20hotel%20in%20London%20and%20an%20art%20collection%20including%20a%20%24250%20million%20Cezanne%20and%20a%20%24179%20million%20Picasso%20have%20raised%20their%20international%20profile.%20Qatar%20has%20had%20its%20share%20of%20investment%20flops.%20The%20QIA%20owned%20a%206.8%25%20stake%20in%20Credit%20Suisse%20Group%20AG%20and%20lost%20roughly%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20last%20year%20when%20the%20financial%20giant%20collapsed.%20The%20fund%20also%20has%20an%20interest%20in%20London's%20struggling%20Canary%20Wharf%2C%20which%20required%20a%20%26amp%3B%23163%3B400%20million%20(%24506.2%20million)%20cash%20injection%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Royal%20family%20also%20projects%20its%20soft%20power%20as%20a%20benefactor%20of%20education.%20Qatar%20has%20given%20American%20universities%20almost%20%246%20billion%2C%20vastly%20more%20than%20any%20other%20country%2C%20according%20to%20a%20Bloomberg%20analysis%20of%20US%20Department%20of%20Education%20data.%20Cornell%20University%2C%20which%20opened%20an%20outpost%20of%20its%20medical%20school%20in%20Doha%2C%20was%20the%20biggest%20recipient%2C%20disclosing%20almost%20%242%20billion%20in%20gifts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESheikha%20Moza%20bint%20Nasser%20Al%20Misnad%2C%20mother%20of%20the%20current%20emir%2C%20chairs%20the%20family's%20education-focused%20philanthropy%2C%20the%20Qatar%20Foundation.%20Qatar%20has%20also%20donated%20to%20primary%20schools%2C%20high-profile%20think%20tanks%20and%20humanitarian%20projects%20in%20places%20as%20far-flung%20as%20Brazil%2C%20Cambodia%20and%20Niger.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20250-acre%20campus%20on%20the%20outskirts%20of%20Doha%20called%20Education%20City%2C%20the%20foundation%20has%20built%20local%20branches%20of%20seven%20elite%20foreign%20universities%20including%20Cornell%2C%20Georgetown%20and%20Northwestern.%20(Texas%20A%26amp%3BM%20announced%20in%20February%20that%20it%20wasn't%20renewing%20its%20Qatar%20Foundation%20partnership%2C%20citing%20regional%20instability.)%20The%20partnerships%20and%20other%20donations%20have%20%C2%ADprovided%20welcome%20revenue%20for%20colleges%20but%20also%20sparked%20concern%20about%20academic%20freedom%20and%20the%20influence%20of%20a%20foreign%20agenda.%20Cornell%20and%20Northwestern%20say%20they're%20benefiting%20the%20region%3B%20other%20schools%20declined%20to%20answer%20questions%20or%20respond.%20The%20Qatari%20official%20statement%20calls%20those%20criticisms%20part%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bdisinformation%20campaign%26quot%3B%20about%20its%20partnerships%20with%20prestigious%20colleges.%20%26quot%3BEducation%20should%20always%20be%20focused%20on%20the%20best%20interests%20of%20students%20and%20their%20pursuit%20of%20knowledge%2C%20and%20above%20vested%20interests%20and%20harmful%20influences%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20statement%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-04%2F89dq3058_qatar-royal-family-bloomberg-_625x300_14_April_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPhoto%20Credit%3A%20Bloomberg%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20absolute%20rulers%20of%20a%20state%20with%20fewer%20than%20400%2C000%20citizens-the%20rest%20of%20the%20population%20comprises%20expatriates%20and%20guest%20workers-the%20Al%20Thanis%20have%20to%20keep%20an%20eye%20on%20their%20position%20at%20home%20by%20minding%20their%20relations%20with%20influential%20local%20business%20families%20and%20other%20Qatari%20tribal%20clans%2C%20according%20to%20the%20people%20who%20know%20the%20leadership.%20Projects%20are%20evenly%20distributed%20among%20these%20factions%2C%20and%20the%20deputy%20emir%20is%20responsible%20for%20keeping%20the%20tribes%20happy%2C%20the%20people%20say.%20It's%20a%20way%20of%20warding%20off%20threats%20in%20a%20family%20that's%20seen%20its%20share%20of%20coups%2C%20most%20recently%20in%201995%2C%20when%20Hamad%20deposed%20his%20father%20while%20he%20was%20abroad%20in%20Switzerland.%20The%20family%2C%20despite%20numbering%20in%20the%20thousands%2C%20can%20amply%20provide%20for%20each%20member%2C%20thus%20cementing%20the%20position%20of%20the%20main%20ruling%20branch.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20increase%20in%20LNG%20capacity%20marks%20the%20next%20phase%20of%20Qatar's%20development.%20The%20goal%20is%20to%20make%20the%20country%20more%20of%20a%20tourist%20destination%2C%20as%20well%20as%20increase%20the%20Qatari%20population%20to%201%20million.%20Progress%20is%20slow%2C%20derailed%20by%20the%20war%20in%20Gaza%20and%20an%20economic%20slowdown%20following%20the%20frenzy%20of%20soccer's%20World%20Cup%2C%20which%20Qatar%20hosted%20in%202022.%20The%20country%20overbuilt%20before%20the%20big%20event%2C%20and%20real%20estate%20prices%20have%20flatlined.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20process%20leading%20to%20its%20winning%20World%20Cup%20bid%20in%202010%20tarnished%20Qatar's%20reputation%2C%20kicking%20off%20years%20of%20scrutiny%20over%20human%20rights%20and%20corruption%20investigations.%20In%20a%202020%20indictment%2C%20the%20US%20accused%20three%20executives%20at%20the%20sport's%20governing%20body%2C%20FIFA%2C%20of%20taking%20bribes%20from%20Qatar.%20By%20then%20two%20had%20died%2C%20and%20the%20third%2C%20who%20denied%20the%20charges%2C%20couldn't%20be%20extradited%20from%20Brazil.%20FIFA%20cleared%20Qatar%20of%20wrongdoing%20in%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20vibe%20in%20Doha%20these%20days%20is%20subdued%2C%20a%20city%20waiting%20to%20find%20out%20where%20it%20goes%20next.%20Many%20foreign%20companies%20and%20law%20firms%20are%20shrinking%20their%20local%20offices%2C%20and%20expats%20are%20leaving.%20Once-hot%20restaurants%20are%20luring%20diners%20with%20cut-rate%20deals.%20%26quot%3BSuddenly%20there's%20no%20new%20horizon%20to%20look%20forward%20to%2C%26quot%3B%20Cinzia%20Bianco%2C%20a%20fellow%20at%20the%20European%20Council%20on%20Foreign%20Relations%2C%20says%20about%20the%20mood%20in%20Doha.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20sense%2C%20like%20after%20you're%20drunk%20on%20enthusiasm%2C%20you're%20a%20little%20bit%20down.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Al%20Thanis'%20wealth%20will%20go%20a%20long%20way%20toward%20cushioning%20the%20country%20from%20any%20slump.%20As%20the%20massive%20expansion%20of%20Qatar's%20LNG%20plant%20accelerates%20and%20turmoil%20from%20the%20Qatari%20embargo%20fades%2C%20the%20family%20is%20looking%20more%20powerful%20than%20ever.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20Saudis%20and%20Emiratis%20hoped%20to%20split%20the%20family%2C%20it%20had%20the%20opposite%20effect%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Kristian%20Coates%20Ulrichsen%2C%20a%20fellow%20at%20Rice%20University's%20Baker%20Institute%20for%20Public%20Policy.%20%26quot%3BQatar%20and%20the%20Al%20Thanis%20are%20probably%20more%20cohesive%20than%20they've%20ever%20been.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713070860000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-04%2F27r30pd_emir-of-qatar_625x300_14_April_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fqatar-royal-family-a-150-billion-fortune-and-art-of-diplomatic-mediation-5437967%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20only-in-Qatar%20milieu%20embodies%20how%20the%20royal%20family%20parlays%20its%20wealth%20into%20geopolitical%20influence%2C%20most%20recently%20as%20a%20key%20mediator%20for%20the%20Israel-Hamas%20war.%20The%20rulers%20have%20turned%20Qatar%20into%20a%20vital%20energy%20supplier%2C%20prominent%20i